Australian Dollar Weakens Versus U.S. Dollar, Yen After U.S. Ratings Cut

-- B y   G a r f i e l d   R e y n o l d s
-- 
2011-08-07T19:46:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-07/australian-dollar-weakens-versus-u-s-dollar-yen-after-u-s-ratings-cut.html
The Australian dollar fell againsst
the yen and the U.S. dollar on speculation investors will sell
higher-yielding assets after  Standard & Poor’s  lowered the
U.S.’s credit rating.  The so-called Aussie touched as low as $1.0378 before
trading at $1.0413 as of 5:45 a.m. in Sydney, from $1.0442 on
Aug. 5 in  New York . It slid to as low as NZ$1.2340, the weakest
since July 29, 2010 and was at NZ$1.2383 from NZ$1.2384.  The Australian dollar fell 0.8 percent to 81.20 yen and the
New Zealand currency declined 0.9 percent to 65.55 yen.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Garfield Reynolds in Sydney at 
